                            <comment id="13139456" author="stack" created="Sat, 29 Oct 2011 21:38:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You have any example of this Prakash.  Sounds pretty bad.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13139857" author="khemani" created="Mon, 31 Oct 2011 02:02:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Stack, it is pretty obvious in the code. And yes, I have had seen lost&lt;br/&gt;
edits a number of times.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple way to reproduce this issue&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Create a table&lt;br/&gt;
Kill namenode. That kills all region servers.&lt;br/&gt;
Master doesn&apos;t die.&lt;br/&gt;
Master tries to split logs and fails. But it ignores the failure and moves&lt;br/&gt;
on to assign regions.&lt;br/&gt;
Start namenode.&lt;br/&gt;
Start regionservers&lt;br/&gt;
The regions get assigned w/o their logs getting replayed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;==&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW, the fix to this is being posted by Nicolas in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2312&quot; title=&quot;Possible data loss when RS goes into GC pause while rolling HLog&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2312&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2312&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;




</comment>
                            <comment id="13140302" author="stack" created="Mon, 31 Oct 2011 16:50:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Prakash Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13143598" author="nspiegelberg" created="Thu, 3 Nov 2011 23:19:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2312&quot; title=&quot;Possible data loss when RS goes into GC pause while rolling HLog&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2312&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2312&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
